                            I really enjoy the learning resources shared by the tutors. They’re engaging, easy to follow, and always connect well with what we’re covering in class. 
                            The best part is that I was able to message the tutor directly to ask questions and get a follow-up on the resource they posted. It feels like getting extra 
                            guidance outside of lessons, and the quick responses make studying much more effective. 
                            Having this kind of support keeps me motivated and makes learning much more enjoyable.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <button class="carousel-control-prev" type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExampleControlsNoTouching" data-bs-slide="prev">
                <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                <span class="visually-hidden">Previous</span>
            </button>
            <button class="carousel-control-next" type="button" data-bs-target="#carouselExampleControlsNoTouching" data-bs-slide="next">
                <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                <span class="visually-hidden">Next</span>
            </button>
        </div>
    </div>
 </div>




<script>
        const quotes = [
        "The expert in anything was once a beginner. – Helen Hayes",
        "Success is not about being the best. It's about being better than you were yesterday. – Unknown",
        "Education is not preparation for life; education is life itself. – John Dewey",
        "The only way to do great work is to love what you do. – Steve Jobs",
        "Learning never exhausts the mind. – Leonardo da Vinci",
        "Your limitation—it's only your imagination. Push yourself, because no one else is going to do it for you. – Unknown",
        "The future belongs to those who learn more skills and combine them in creative ways. – Robert Greene",
        "Don't let what you cannot do interfere with what you can do. – John Wooden",
        "The beautiful thing about learning is that no one can take it away from you. – B.B. King",
        "Success is the sum of small efforts repeated day in and day out. – Robert Collier",
        "The capacity to learn is a gift; the ability to learn is a skill; the willingness to learn is a choice. – Brian Herbert",
        "IT'S HOW WE ARE WIRED ~ Belgium Campus"
    ];

    let currentQuoteIndex = 0;
    const quoteDisplay = document.getElementById('quoteDisplay');

    function showNextQuote() {
        currentQuoteIndex = (currentQuoteIndex + 1) % quotes.length;
        quoteDisplay.textContent = quotes[currentQuoteIndex];
    }

    // Change quote every 3.5 seconds
    setInterval(showNextQuote, 5500);
</script>